<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
  com.miningguardian.scanner.plist (PR I-2 / Bucket-3 installer)

  launchd LaunchDaemon for the main Mining Guardian scan loop on macOS.
  Mirrors the systemd unit `mining-guardian.service` running today on the
  ROBS-PC + VPS pair (cutover scope γ — Mini replaces both).

  Install path: copied by postinstall.sh to
      /Library/LaunchDaemons/com.miningguardian.scanner.plist
  and loaded with:
      sudo launchctl bootstrap system <path-to-plist>

  Path + env conventions (matches PR #41 feedback-loop-daemon plist):
    install root              /Library/Application Support/MiningGuardian
    .env (private secrets)    /Library/Application Support/MiningGuardian/.env
    venv                      /Library/Application Support/MiningGuardian/venv
    launcher wrapper          /Library/Application Support/MiningGuardian/bin/scanner_launcher.sh
    logs                      /Library/Application Support/MiningGuardian/logs/

  The wrapper exists because launchd has no EnvironmentFile= equivalent;
  the wrapper sources .env then execs python.

  Recurrence (P-039, 2026-05-11)
  ==============================
  The scanner is a long-running daemon. The launcher passes the loop
  flag to core/mining_guardian.py, which iterates internally every
  `scan_interval_seconds` (read from config.json / .env). Under normal
  operation the daemon stays alive between scans so the 8 in-process AI
  features (outcome checker, HVAC correlation, daily deep dive scheduling,
  local LLM analyzer threads, etc.) can run after each scan.

  Recurrence layers:
    1. RunAtLoad=true               : launchd starts the daemon on boot
                                       and on `launchctl bootstrap`.
    2. Internal `while True` loop   : daemon sleeps scan_interval_seconds
       in `loop()`                    between scans. Honors .env.
    3. KeepAlive.Crashed=true       : launchd re-launches if the daemon
                                       crashes (non-zero exit).
    4. StartInterval=3600           : SAFETY NET. If the daemon ever exits
                                       cleanly (which should not happen in
                                       loop mode), launchd re-launches it
                                       within one hour. While the daemon is
                                       alive, launchd skips re-launches.

  Why StartInterval was missing before P-039
  ==========================================
  Bug history: prior to P-039 the launcher exec'd python WITHOUT loop mode,
  so the daemon performed a single `run_once()` and exited successfully.
  KeepAlive only matched Crashed=true, so the clean exit was not retried,
  and no StartInterval existed to re-launch on a clock. Result: one scan
  per `launchctl bootstrap`, then silence overnight. Detected during the
  2026-05-10/11 VPS+ROBS-PC isolation crossover (Mini scan #25/#26 only
  ran after manual `launchctl kickstart`). P-039 fixes both the launcher
  (adds the loop flag) and the plist (adds StartInterval as a belt-and-
  suspenders safety net).

  Why launchd cannot read scan_interval_seconds from .env
  =======================================================
  launchd plists are static XML loaded by the system before any Mining
  Guardian process runs. There is no EnvironmentFile= equivalent to
  systemd. The daemon's internal loop reads .env-driven config at runtime
  via core/models.py: that is the authoritative cadence for normal
  operation. The plist's StartInterval is a packaged hourly safety net
  matching the documented "1 scan per hour" cadence in CLAUDE.md and
  AI_ROADMAP.md (`scan_interval_seconds: 3600`). It is intentionally not
  shorter than the documented cadence: it should never fire under normal
  operation.
-->
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN"
  "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>Label</key>
    <string>com.miningguardian.scanner</string>

    <key>ProgramArguments</key>
    <array>
        <string>/bin/bash</string>
        <string>/Library/Application Support/MiningGuardian/bin/scanner_launcher.sh</string>
    </array>

    <key>WorkingDirectory</key>
    <string>/Library/Application Support/MiningGuardian</string>

    <key>RunAtLoad</key>
    <true/>

    <key>KeepAlive</key>
    <dict>
        <key>SuccessfulExit</key>
        <false/>
        <key>Crashed</key>
        <true/>
    </dict>

    <!--
      P-039 (2026-05-11) — recurrence safety net.
      Under normal operation the daemon stays alive between scans (launcher
      passes the loop flag). StartInterval only fires if the daemon exits
      cleanly somehow; it is the belt-and-suspenders backstop for the
      overnight-no-scan bug found during the 2026-05-10 isolation crossover.
    -->
    <key>StartInterval</key>
    <integer>3600</integer>

    <key>ThrottleInterval</key>
    <integer>10</integer>

    <key>ProcessType</key>
    <string>Standard</string>

    <key>StandardOutPath</key>
    <string>/Library/Application Support/MiningGuardian/logs/scanner.out.log</string>

    <key>StandardErrorPath</key>
    <string>/Library/Application Support/MiningGuardian/logs/scanner.err.log</string>

    <key>EnvironmentVariables</key>
    <dict>
        <key>PYTHONUNBUFFERED</key>
        <string>1</string>
        <key>PATH</key>
        <string>/Library/Application Support/MiningGuardian/venv/bin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin</string>
    </dict>
</dict>
</plist>
